<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Sunday posts from Gordon Wrinn</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=193016" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000136.html">Gordon: Fatties are getting the shaft in equipment</a></B><P>

I'm a rather large warrior. We all know the big boys are the best when it comes to the real fighting and yet day by day I see my brothers left in the cold in regards to equipment.<P>

<B>There should be some advantages for those who choose to forego the immense advantages that come with choosing to be a large race.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000542.html">What was the Original Fiery Avenger Quest?</a></B><P>

It was said that there was one. Then it was said that it was taken out as no one had solved it and they made the new one.
So, what was the original?<P>

<B>I'm sorry, but as we might implement another quest in a similar fashion in the future, we can't release the information in regards to the old quest. However, I can say that you certainly wouldn't have gotten it by "hailing the right NPC", much like the current quest.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001076.html">Gordon- Vermaculated armor once again</a></B><P>

Vermaculated armor once again<P>

<B>This issue has been addressed with the Live Team several times, and the outcome is that the stats on these items are intentional. As such, we're closing the issue.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001197.html">Abashi Advocates "Taxi Services in Everquest"</a></B><P>

In reality of the situation EQ is in poor design, and the time constraints are absurd.<P>

<B>I advocate people grouping with classes that can provide benefits that are not available to their own class. If you want to minimize the usefulness of this ability and call it "Taxi Service", I suppose you can do that.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001224.html">Moss Covered Twig</a></B><P>

Can you confirm or deny if you are going to nerf this weapon yet? <P>

<B>We still haven't made a descision regarding these extremely low-delay weapons yet. We'll be sure to publicize it when the decision has been made.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001228.html">Always wondered about this....</a></B><P>

I've recently seen a lot of talk about a server where lvl'ing would be much easier and items would be easier to obtain as well. <P>

<B>We talk about this in the FAQ at </B><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html">everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html</a><B>. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001229.html">Too many people on a sever? What to do now?</a></B><P>

Do you think there is a way to make respawn times faster on 'full' servers?<P>

<B>Unfortuantely, that's not the answer to overcrowding. Lack of things to kill in a particular area is one of the things that gets people to spread out to some of the other areas in the game. There is now more than enough land and things to kill in the game to support well over two thousand people, though as we mentioned before, we're not raising the official peak-usage target.<P>

The other issue is that dungeons are laid out so that if they are "done" (rather than camped), several groups can move through them and get enough time to rest. Increasing spawn times, by even a minute, upsets that balance and actually promotes camping.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001231.html">Lore Items..</a></B><P>

Supposedly an item with the LORE ITEM tag is supposed to have info on it that can be revealed with an Identify. But most lore items either dont need a description because it is inherent in the title, or are lore simply to prevent a user from having more than one at a time(magician summoned staffs come quickly to mind)<P>

The other day I looted a guard bracer of a fallen guard. Th item was no drop, but not lore. I had heard about a guard bracer quest and that to turn in the wrong bracer meant death.. so I decided to give Identify a shot. Item Lore:Loyal Guard Bracer. Or something. So apparently Lore has nothing to do with hidden info about an item.<P>

<B>I think that we're going to begin adding actual "lore" to those lore items soon. We have a writer on the EQ Live staff who will probably take that up soon.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001241.html">Gordon Look! :) Mana Regen Again ....</a></B><P>

I've noticed that it is taking FOREVER to med with my skill stuck at 255 (or 252?). We continue to get more mana intensive spells and more mana past the level 50 mark, but I am stuck with the same med capability I will have at level 60 that I had at level 50. So is there a fix proposed for this?<P>

<B>The "solution" for what you are mentioning is grouping with classes that have the ability to increase your regen rate. Bards and enchanters can do this for you, and can certainly increase it at a rate beyond what it was at level 50.<P>

Putting in other ways to increase mana regeneration would unbalance the game. The methods available to increase the rate of regeneration do so to the greatest extent that we've designed for the game.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001243.html">The easiest way to silence post-50 monk complaints</a></B><P>

Simply put, give us triple attack at 60 like the warriors. We will be able to outdamage them again by a significant margin. Our lower ac won't be as big an issue because groups will want us again for our damage output.<BR>
Come on Verant.<P>

<B>Triple attack is basically just "something neat". I don't understand why this is a frequent point with monks, as it really doesn't fire that often for warriors to really swing balance. If monks want it just because it's a skill that they don't have, that's really not a compelling reason to add it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001244.html">Magicians</a></B><P>

Can us mages get some "fun" spells put into the game? Perhaps find a way to spice up the class without unbalancing it? <P>

<B>I thought we did some of that with the bundle/pack spells that we threw in. They are really there just for fun, as you suggest. If you can think of some other "fun" spells, we could throw those in as well :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001246.html">Post 50 cleric spell order screwed up -- clerics constantly told Verant, and still!</a></B><P>

When people started to get their hands on expansion spell lists, lots of clerics scratched their heads. The group resolution spell is given levels after the group heroism spell, which is significantly better. This was obviously a fluke, and so countless clerics, low and high level alike, brought this up in countless threads regarding the expansion spells.<P>

<B>They were initially correct towards the end of the RoK beta, however at some point they got messed up. You are right that a few are out of order, for instance, with group heroism coming before group resolution. <P>

Rather than just put them in the right order, which would be considered as a nerf by some, we're going to just change a spell or two to something more appropriate for the level. For instance, I believe that we are changing "United Resolve" to a "group symbol" spell that only uses one component.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001253.html">Didn't you say roleplay showed up?</a></B><P>

If you do a /who all 'guild' you show up. Well guess what? I'm in a guild, I put on roleplay and I didnt show up. My friend in a different guild didn't show up either...<P>

<B>That's what the patch message said, unfortunately one file that was needed for the change to go active wasn't included in the patch. It will be in the next.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001623.html">RUMOR!! If it's true I will never play EQ again</a></B><P>

I noticed Abashi has been hanging around I hope to get a response as to whats up with Feign Death.<P>

<B>Nothing is "up" with it to my knowledge. We certianly haven't discussed any changes with it in tuning meetings. If any change has really happened on the test server, please let me know.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

according to people I know and things that have been derived from the test server atmopsphere Feign death has an added recast time to it, so feigns cannot be done in succession.<P>

<B>Interestingly enough, that was a suggestion that was made here on the boards a while back to eliminate feign-pulling: Make it so that the recycle timer doesn't start until you stand up. <P>

In any case, we haven't implemented it. I checked out feign quite a bit during the last great-feign debate, and also just checked it now, and it appears to be the same to me.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001700.html">Abashi - Whats the ETA on the Disease line being upgraded?</a></B><P>

Long ago, when the shaman disease line was changed, we were told to expect 'something interesting' added to them! We're still waiting.<P>

<B>I'm not really sure what may have been indicated in the past in regards to this line. As of now, the disease line is considered adequate. The extended duration of the spells was intentional, and is balanced with the environment.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001772.html">Just a Thanks for the item dropping while switching fix.</a></B><P>

I have posted a several complaints and suggestions since Beta, but rarely a thank you.
Well here it is, Thanks a TON for the item dropping fix for all of us who play bards.<P>

<B>No problem :) I'm glad that we were able to implement it, and likewise pleased that it was well-received by the players.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001782.html">ABASHI - The reasons for all this hostility from people.. minus me :)</a></B><P>

Thundaro here.. Ok i think the biggest problem abashi is, well let me say first: I think you guys are doing an above average job considering the sheer numbers of people you guys have to listen too.. but all that being said heres your problem. Your sick of hearing all the complaints. your sick of hearing things youve heard thousands of times over, and i could relate to that. BUT (ok, HERES the problem :) ) , when you asnwer something you answer in very Condescending way. its like your talking down upon us.. and it shows. tho subtle at times, it shows. Just be honest. <P>

<B>I appreciate the constructive criticism. It's certianly not my intention to be condescending in my responses. Often what happens is that I'm called on to explain the same issue repeatedly, based upon a previous response not being informative enough. I end up trying to explain it with analogies, which are sometimes viewed as condescending in nature, in hopes of getting universal buy-in on the subject. Perhaps the best route would be to explain certain things as best I can once or twice, and stop short of analogizing to the point that the response would be construed as being patronzing.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001800.html">The only Thing I have ever or will ever ask of you Verant/Abashi</a></B><P>

PLEEEEAAAAASSSSSEEE! Could you make it so my Lupine claw gauntlet's are visible when I wear them! <P>

<B>As they are hand items, they cannot appear as a model held in the hand such as thulian claws. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001804.html">Gordon, if you would be so kind.....</a></B><P>

Pestilence Scythe, 2H slash ok? SK NEC WAR but Necro's can't slash <P>

<B>The inclusions of necromancers on this item was most likely a mistake. That said, they look pretty cool when wielded by a caster. When the SolRo quests first came out, the first thing I did with my necro was to run out and get a Harvester :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

A more important question is how in the world this post (which is a fair, albeit minor question) gets a response within 2 minutes of being posted while the more substantive customer service thread gets none?<P>

<B>Because I happen to be sitting at home, looking at the boards in my off-time when it was posted. Please don't follow me around to threads I post in demanding I address some other issue. It isn't polite.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001805.html">Abashi: Why are threads not addressed to you or verant being closed?</a></B><P>

This thread discusses a dead issue, but its not addressed to verant or you. I though players were still allowed to discuss these issues?<P>

<B>Oops, your right. I took it as being implicitly addressed to us. Upon rereading it, it apparently wasn't. I've reopened the thread and deleted my post from it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001807.html">Abashi: Casual Player Server? Ideas from a power gamer.</a></B><P>

Okay, so let's define casual. I'm gonna go with the guy who plays from 0 to 20 hours a week. He logs on, wants to play for a bit, but can't because the game -is- designed around sitting down for at -least- a 4 hour session unless you're a soloist class.<P>

So what do I have in mind? Create a server with radically different programming. <P>

<B>Hi there,<P>

This issue is discussed in the FAQ. The average EQ player typically plays around 20 hours per week, so overall advancement is based somewhat upon that figure. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

How do you know its 20 hours a week? Please define the source of that datum.<P>

<B>It's actually over 20 hours per week, much closer to 23. The data is fairly easy to come by, as we can tell who is logged into the servers at any given time, and how long they are logged in.</B><P>

That 20 hour figure is fine if you reduce the weak to two days. I play about 20 hours a week myself, but that's based on the fact that I put in all 20 in one session, and then take a long break. Not everybody is as fortunate as me to have a nice schedule.<P>

<B>I know what you are saying. That's pretty typical of the average player. The average player typically plays a few hours each day with one long session once or twice a week.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001810.html">Suggestions to Verant for the message board...</a></B><P>

I don't know if it's possible code-wise with these boards, but the Crossroads boards have a nice feature which allows you to mark your posts so all replies are sent to you via email as well as posted. <P>

<B>We have someone who is going to be writing new messageboard scripts. While UBB is nice, it lacks some features which we need on boards with this much traffic. It is possible that that might be an option that we include. I'm supposed to have a design meeting with the programmer who's doing the scripts in the near future, and I'll bring it up.<P>

-Gordon</b><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001813.html">Quoting Gordon (A new pasttime?)</a></B><P>

You have previously stated that other items are "dead" yet have found yourself to be mistaken and corrected them. Alchemy and Mage pet dual wield the two most visible examples.<P>

<B>Alchemy was before my time, but with the mage pet issue, it was only a couple of days from the time that that thread was initially addressed and the time that the issue was acknowledged and fixed. I'd initially tested the issue, and thought they were dual wielding, but upon continued info coming from the players I changed my testing methodology and determed that they weren't dual-wielding.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/001814.html">Deleting petitions.</a></B><P>

No doubt many people including myself have made petitions, only to be able to resolve the situation themselves or with help from other players moments later before a GM was able to reply. <P>

Unfortunately once the problem has been solved, the petition is still waiting, and the sender has no way of removing the petition from the que, or informing the GM`s that they no longer need assistance, which no doubt is a waste of they're time, and players who still need help are left waiting longer.<P>

Is there any chance that a means of deleting petitions sent would be added to the game?<P>

<B>That's a good idea. I'll mention it to the team.<P>

Players can currently only file one petition per character. A "delete petition" command (e.g. /delpetition) would just inform the server that you are no longer in need of help allowing the server to expire the petition.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
