	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ermmm not sure I agree with the logic that &quot;Well you have an advantage being big - so you get*****ed when it comes to item selection.&quot;  Along with the advantage of size come some serious disadvantages, not the least of which is KOS in a majority of places. (Which forces you to be VERY careful where you hunt and move).<BR>
<BR>
A race composed of fighters, witchdoctors, and dark god worshipping warriors would have, over time, created, manufactured or developed items and weapons suitable for use by their kind only.  <BR>
<BR>
These items would fall into one of two categories:<BR>
1) Items which augment current abilities (Strength, Stamina)<BR>
2) Items which augment existing weaknesses (Dex, Charisma, Agility, Intelligence)<BR>
<BR>
Smaller races have their advantages too - speed, quickness and decent faction.  Yet if there is a plethora of items available for them that is NOT available for Ogres, Trolls, Barbarians - erm again - don't see the logic in that.  <BR>
<BR>
(In many mythologies it was the underground races - Dwarves (Durin from Norse) or Trolls (Can't quote example off top of my head) that made great warrior items.)  Verant isn't mythology - but I don't see where penalizing a race for size is equitable.<BR>
<BR>
(And I play a Barbarian Shaman - so I have no stake in this either way)<BR>
<BR>
Faern<BR>
Tarew Marr<BR>
Shaman fo the 35th year of the Wolf
				</font>
